content:
Considerations for Enhanced Bots

Carefully review these considerations before setting up Enhanced Bots.

Enhanced bots connect to Messaging for In-App and Web, Facebook Messenger, and WhatsApp enhanced Messaging channels, and to Slack and the Einstein Bots API. Enhanced bots are subject to Messaging channel specifications and don’t use Chat-only features.

To route to agents, bots, queues, and skills, enhanced bots use Omni-Channel Flow. To route to Slack and the Einstein Bots API, enhanced bots use connections. Enhanced bots support direct bot-to-bot transfers to other enhanced bots only.

You can create an enhanced bot only from templates created with the enhanced bot type or created from an existing enhanced bot.

Post-Chat URLs aren’t supported for enhanced bots.

Bot session inactivity time limits depend on the channel type.

Messaging Components in Enhanced Bots

Support for messaging components varies by channel. The authentication, custom, and payment components are supported only for enhanced Apple Messages for Business channels. The form component is supported for Apple Messages for Business and Messaging for In-App and Web.

The Einstein Bots API doesn’t support messaging components. Custom constants in messaging components aren’t supported. Translation of messaging components isn't supported.
title: Configuring Enhanced Bots in Service Cloud
